<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="189" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,1436,1967]" pageId="6" pageNumber="189">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,1508,1534]" pageId="6" pageNumber="189">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This new species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="(Zheng, 2005)" authorityName="Zhang &amp; Deng &amp; Li &amp; Lin" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Zheng" baseAuthorityYear="2005" box="[683,1077,1508,1535]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Xistra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="189" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lochengensis">
<emphasis box="[683,905,1508,1534]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="189">Xistra lochengensis</emphasis>
(Zheng, 2005)
</taxonomicName>
from which it differs in lateral margins of vertex reaching the level of upper margin of eyes (lateral margins of vertex slightly exerted above upper margin of eyes in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zhang &amp; Deng &amp; Li &amp; Lin" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Zheng" baseAuthorityYear="2005" box="[355,531,1580,1606]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Xistra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="189" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lochengensis">
<emphasis box="[355,531,1580,1606]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="189">X. lochengensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); frontal costa straight between lateral ocelli (frontal costa concave between lateral ocelli in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zhang &amp; Deng &amp; Li &amp; Lin" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Zheng" baseAuthorityYear="2005" box="[299,475,1616,1642]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Xistra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="189" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lochengensis">
<emphasis box="[299,475,1616,1642]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="189">X. lochengensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); in profile, upper margin of pronotum straight (in profile, upper margin of pronotum undulating in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zhang &amp; Deng &amp; Li &amp; Lin" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Zheng" baseAuthorityYear="2005" box="[305,481,1652,1678]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Xistra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="189" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lochengensis">
<emphasis box="[305,481,1652,1678]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="189">X. lochengensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); middle femur wider than visible part of tegmen in width (middle femur equal to visible part of tegmen in width in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zhang &amp; Deng &amp; Li &amp; Lin" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Zheng" baseAuthorityYear="2005" box="[497,672,1688,1714]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Xistra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="189" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lochengensis">
<emphasis box="[497,672,1688,1714]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="189">X. lochengensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). It is also similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Li, Deng &amp; Zheng, 2014" authorityName="Li, Deng &amp; Zheng" authorityYear="2014" box="[909,1394,1688,1715]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Xistra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="189" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brachynota">
<emphasis box="[909,1112,1688,1714]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="189">Xistra brachynota</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Li, X. D. &amp; Deng, W. A. &amp; Zheng, Z. M. &amp; Lin, M. P. &amp; Lu, C. W." box="[1118,1394,1688,1715]" pageId="6" pageNumber="189" pagination="209 - 217" refId="ref10333" refString="Li, X. D., Deng, W. A., Zheng, Z. M., Lin, M. P. &amp; Lu, C. W. (2014) Two new species of the genus Xistra Bolivar (Orthoptera: tetrigidae) from China. Neotropical Entomology, 43, 209 - 217. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / s 13744 - 014 - 0197 - x" type="journal article" year="2014">Li, Deng &amp; Zheng, 2014</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
but differs from the latter by width of each eye 1.5 times wider than width of vertex (width of each eye 2.0 times wider than width of vertex in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Li, Deng &amp; Zheng" authorityYear="2014" box="[420,580,1760,1786]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Xistra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="189" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brachynota">
<emphasis box="[420,580,1760,1786]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="189">X. brachynota</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); width of longitudinal furrow of frontal ridge very narrower than antennal groove diameter (width of longitudinal furrow of frontal ridge equal to antennal groove diameter in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Li, Deng &amp; Zheng" authorityYear="2014" box="[1261,1420,1796,1822]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Xistra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="189" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brachynota">
<emphasis box="[1261,1420,1796,1822]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="189">X. brachynota</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); dorsal and ventral margins of fore and middle femora undulated (dorsal and ventral margins of fore and middle femora straight in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Li, Deng &amp; Zheng" authorityYear="2014" box="[357,516,1868,1894]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Xistra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="189" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brachynota">
<emphasis box="[357,516,1868,1894]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="189">X. brachynota</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
